### Upload Media (JPEG Example)
# Uploads a JPEG image to the media store.
# The system generates medium and small thumbnails automatically.
# @name uploadMediaJpeg
POST {{host}}/api/media/upload
Content-Type: multipart/form-data; boundary=boundary

--boundary
Content-Disposition: form-data; name="files[]"; filename="image.jpg"

# Replace "< /path/to/your/image.jpg" with the actual path to your file
< /path/to/your/image.jpg
--boundary--

### Expected Response (Success - 200 OK):
# Content-Type: application/json
#
# {
#   "full": "/api/media?p=/path/to/image.jpg",
#   "medium": "/api/media?p=/path/to/image_m.jpg",
#   "small": "/api/media?p=/path/to/image_s.jpg"
# }


### Upload Media (PNG Example)
# Uploads a PNG image to the media store.
# @name uploadMediaPng
POST {{host}}/api/media/upload
Content-Type: multipart/form-data; boundary=boundary

--boundary
Content-Disposition: form-data; name="files[]"; filename="photo.png"

# Replace "< /path/to/your/image.png" with the actual path to your file
< /path/to/your/image.png
--boundary--

### Expected Response (Success - 200 OK):
# Content-Type: application/json


### Get Media File
# Retrieves a media file (original or thumbnail) from the store.
# @name getMedia
GET {{host}}/api/media?p=/path/to/image.jpg

### Expected Response (Success - 200 OK):
# Content-Type: image/jpeg (or appropriate mimetype)
# (Binary image data)

### Expected Response (Error - 404 Not Found):
# If the file does not exist.
# HTTP/1.1 404 Not Found